        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 7:29PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 728 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Garland, which is 10 miles southeast of Powell,
moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts 40 to 50 mph and pea sized hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Big
Horn and northeastern Park Counties, including the following
locations... Cowley, North Big Horn County Airport, Lovell, and
Bighorn Canyon National Recreation Area.

Other showers and thunderstorms across the north half of Big Horn
County will be capable of producing wind gusts around 40 mph.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. If you are
on Bighorn Lake, move to shore and off the water.</instruction>
